    "ci_concept": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"ci-feature-shell\">\n  <section class=\"ci-section\">\n    <div class=\"ci-wrap\">\n      <div class=\"ci-section-head\">\n        <p class=\"ci-kicker\">The Concept</p>\n        <h2>Sound Shaped to Your Anatomy</h2>\n        <p>A Custom In-Ear Monitor (CIEM) is a high-performance audio device engineered for the unique anatomy of an individual\u2019s ears. Unlike universal in-ear monitors that rely on silicone or foam tips to create a seal inside a standard-shaped ear, a CIEM begins with a medical-grade silicone impression of your ear canal and outer ear. That impression becomes the blueprint for a shell that fits you, and only you.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ci-article-body\">\n        <div class=\"ci-article-copy\">\n          <h3>More than a monitor</h3>\n          <p>The difference between a universal IEM and a custom is not volume. It is seal, stability, and consistency. A properly fitted CIEM sits flush in the concha, follows the contours of your ear canal past the second bend, and creates an acoustic chamber that is identical every time you insert it. This means the sound you hear on stage tonight is the same sound you heard in soundcheck this afternoon.</p>\n          <p>CIEMs are used by performing musicians who need to hear their own mix over a loud stage, by audiophiles who want the most direct and uncoloured signal path, and by audio engineers who require a portable reference they can trust in any control room. The common thread is that the fit is inseparable from the sound: a loose seal changes the bass response, and a shifting monitor changes the stereo image.</p>\n          <p>At AAW, every custom shell is built from a 3D scan of your physical ear impressions. The geometry is modelled in software, printed, and then hand-finished to remove layer lines and ensure a smooth, bio-compatible surface. The result is a monitor that disappears in the ear after a few minutes of wear \u2014 not because the sound is quiet, but because the physical object stops feeling foreign.</p>\n        </div>\n        <figure class=\"ci-article-figure\">\n          <img src=\"{{ 'canary-pro-ciem-pair.jpg' | asset_url }}\" alt=\"AAW Canary Pro custom IEM pair with transparent shells showing internal driver layout\" loading=\"lazy\">\n          <figcaption><b>Canary Pro custom pair</b><span>Transparent shells reveal the multi-driver architecture inside each earpiece.</span></figcaption>\n        </figure>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ci-subhead\">The three pillars of a custom monitor</div>\n      <div class=\"ci-pillar-strip\">\n        <div class=\"ci-pillar\">\n          <div class=\"ci-pillar-icon\">1</div>\n          <h4>The Impression</h4>\n          <p>A silicone cast taken by an audiologist captures the full shape of your ear canal, concha, and helix. A deep, clean impression that passes the second bend is the foundation of a monitor that seals reliably and stays put for hours.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-pillar\">\n          <div class=\"ci-pillar-icon\">2</div>\n          <h4>The Shell</h4>\n          <p>3D-modelled from the scanned impression data, the shell is printed in medical-grade acrylic and hand-finished. It houses the drivers, crossover, and acoustic tubing in a compact volume that follows your ear geometry exactly.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-pillar\">\n          <div class=\"ci-pillar-icon\">3</div>\n          <h4>The Drivers</h4>\n          <p>Balanced armatures, dynamic drivers, or a hybrid of both are placed inside the shell and connected to the nozzle via precision-bore tubing. Each driver handles a specific frequency band, summed by a passive crossover network.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>",
        "content_width": "large",
        "text_alignment": "left",
        "color_scheme": "primary",
        "top_space_desktop": 0,
        "bottom_space_desktop": 0,
        "top_space_mobile": 0,
        "bottom_space_mobile": 0
