    "ci_science": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"ci-feature-shell\">\n  <section class=\"ci-section dark\">\n    <div class=\"ci-wrap\">\n      <div class=\"ci-section-head\">\n        <p class=\"ci-kicker\">The Science</p>\n        <h2>How Custom Monitors Work</h2>\n        <p>The performance of a CIEM rests on four acoustic principles that work together. Understanding them explains why a custom monitor sounds different \u2014 and more consistent \u2014 than any universal alternative.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ci-article-body ci-grid-2 flip\">\n        <figure class=\"ci-article-figure\">\n          <img src=\"{{ 'ash-custom-abalone.jpg' | asset_url }}\" alt=\"AAW custom IEM with abalone shell showing the precision of hand-finished CIEM shells\" loading=\"lazy\">\n          <figcaption><b>Precision shell craft</b><span>Each shell is a sealed acoustic chamber. The wall thickness, nozzle bore, and driver position all affect the final frequency response.</span></figcaption>\n        </figure>\n        <div class=\"ci-article-copy\">\n          <h3>Seal and isolation</h3>\n          <p>A CIEM creates a full-shell acoustic seal deep in the ear canal. Unlike a foam tip that compresses and rebounds inconsistently, a rigid acrylic shell maintains the same insertion depth and seal every time. This passive isolation blocks up to 26 dB of ambient noise \u2014 enough to reduce a 110 dB stage to a comfortable listening level \u2014 without any electronics or batteries.</p>\n          <h3>Driver configuration</h3>\n          <p>AAW CIEMs use balanced armature (BA) drivers, dynamic drivers, or hybrid layouts that combine both. BA drivers are tiny, efficient transducers that excel at detail and speed. Dynamic drivers move more air and deliver sub-bass with physical impact. A multi-driver CIEM dedicates individual drivers to specific frequency ranges \u2014 sub-bass, mid-bass, mids, highs, and super-tweeters \u2014 each optimised for that band.</p>\n          <h3>Crossover and tubing</h3>\n          <p>The crossover is a passive circuit that divides the audio signal into frequency bands and routes each band to the appropriate driver. The length and diameter of the acoustic tubing from each driver to the nozzle further shape the output. This combination of electrical and acoustic filtering is what gives a CIEM its tuning signature \u2014 warm and musical, or flat and analytical, depending on the design.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>",
        "content_width": "large",
        "text_alignment": "left",
        "color_scheme": "primary",
        "top_space_desktop": 0,
        "bottom_space_desktop": 0,
        "top_space_mobile": 0,
        "bottom_space_mobile": 0
      }
    },
    "ci_benefits": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"ci-feature-shell\">\n  <section class=\"ci-section\">\n    <div class=\"ci-wrap\">\n      <div class=\"ci-section-head\">\n        <p class=\"ci-kicker\">Benefits</p>\n        <h2>Why Choose Custom Over Universal</h2>\n        <p>A universal IEM can sound excellent. But a custom IEM sounds excellent every time you put it in. The difference is not always in the driver count or the price tag \u2014 it is in the consistency, comfort, and isolation that only a personalised shell can deliver.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ci-benefit-grid\">\n        <div class=\"ci-benefit-card\">\n          <h3>Perfect Fit</h3>\n          <p>Since the shell is moulded from your own ear impressions, it sits flush against your ear anatomy. No pressure points, no hot spots, and no gradual slipping during movement. The fit is repeatable every time you insert the monitor.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-benefit-card\">\n          <h3>Passive Noise Isolation</h3>\n          <p>A full-shell CIEM blocks up to 26 dB of ambient noise without any electronics. On a loud stage, this means you can monitor at a lower, safer volume. In a caf\u00e9 or on a flight, it means you hear your music, not the engines.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-benefit-card\">\n          <h3>Consistent Sound</h3>\n          <p>Universal tips compress differently each time you insert them, altering the distance between the driver and your eardrum. A rigid CIEM shell holds the drivers in a fixed position relative to your ear, so the frequency response stays identical across sessions.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-benefit-card\">\n          <h3>Long-Session Comfort</h3>\n          <p>Custom shells are worn by musicians for two to three hours on stage without fatigue. The weight is distributed across the concha, and there are no expanding foam or silicone tips pressing outward against the canal walls.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-benefit-card\">\n          <h3>Durable and Repairable</h3>\n          <p>AAW CIEMs are built with serviceable components. Drivers can be replaced, sockets can be repaired, and shells can be reshelled if your ear shape changes over time. A well-maintained CIEM can last a decade or more.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ci-benefit-card\">\n          <h3>Personalised Aesthetics</h3>\n          <p>Choose your shell colour, faceplate material, and artwork. From carbon fibre to abalone, from solid colours to custom engravings, your CIEM looks as individual as it sounds. Every AAW custom order includes a faceplate design consultation.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>",
        "content_width": "large",
        "text_alignment": "left",
        "color_scheme": "primary",
